VALID PARENTHESES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Given a string s containing just the characters:

'('  ')'  '{'  '}'  '['  ']'

Determine if the input string is valid.

A string is valid if:

• Open brackets must be closed by the same type  
• Open brackets must be closed in correct order  
• Every closing bracket has a matching opening bracket  


Example 1:
Input: s = "()"
Output: true


Example 2:
Input: s = "()[]{}"
Output: true


Example 3:
Input: s = "(]"
Output: false


Example 4:
Input: s = "([])"
Output: true


Example 5:
Input: s = "([)]"
Output: false


Constraints:
1 <= s.length <= 10^4
s consists only of '()[]{}'



class Solution {
public:
    bool isValid(string s) 
    {
        stack<char> st;

        for(char ch : s)
        {
            if(ch=='(' || ch=='[' || ch=='{')
            {
                st.push(ch);
            }
            else
            {
                if(st.empty()) return false;

                char top = st.top();
                st.pop();

                if(ch=='}' && top!='{' ||
                   ch==']' && top!='[' ||
                   ch==')' && top!='(')
                    return false;
            }
        }

        return st.empty();
    }
};
